{"name":"Betrayed Ideals for a Superior","pages":[{"sort":100000,"name":"Betrayed Ideals for a Superior","type":"text","_id":"QURuGl6NUu6RXnOo","system":{},"title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<p>The character was placed in a situation where they had to choose between a trusted superior and their own ideals, and they chose to follow the superior.</p><p></p><ul><li><p>ATTRIBUTE: +1 Presence</p></li><li><p>DEPARTMENT: + 1 Command</p></li><li><p>FOCUS SUGGESTIONS: Persuasion, Inspiration, Investigation</p></li></ul>"},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"ownership":{"default":-1,"BsQYuBoOZwvCjdMe":3},"flags":{}}],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.sta.character-lifepath.oxZ5eaIPUpXx8qpS"}},"_stats":{"coreVersion":"10.312","systemId":"sta","systemVersion":"1.2.5","createdTime":1722009465615,"modifiedTime":1724080565424,"lastModifiedBy":"6xWKidE3J8zSAagd"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6xWKidE3J8zSAagd":3},"_id":"EBJ7DJhSimXCzjIf"}
{"name":"Breakthrough or Invention","pages":[{"sort":100000,"name":"Breakthrough or Invention","type":"text","_id":"LO37pEOiHRHeREsC","system":{},"title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<p>The character made an important technological discovery, devised a new way of using a particular technology, or invented some new technology that will be invaluable in the future.</p><p></p><ul><li><p>ATTRIBUTE: +1 Any</p><p></p></li><li><p>DEPARTMENT: + 1 Engineering</p><p></p></li><li><p>FOCUS SUGGESTIONS: Experimental Technology, Invention, or Improvisation</p><p></p></li><li><p>TRAIT: The character may gain trait Inventor of X, where X is the name of the technology invented.</p></li></ul>"},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"ownership":{"default":-1,"BsQYuBoOZwvCjdMe":3},"flags":{}}],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.sta.character-lifepath.CtpQnbJQm0uvHEUi"}},"_stats":{"coreVersion":"10.312","systemId":"sta","systemVersion":"1.2.5","createdTime":1722009493345,"modifiedTime":1724080566912,"lastModifiedBy":"6xWKidE3J8zSAagd"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6xWKidE3J8zSAagd":3},"_id":"6USbKNcihmEQePMN"}
{"name":"Called Out a Superior","pages":[{"sort":100000,"name":"Called Out a Superior","type":"text","_id":"i99VXhwv58qYlQL0","system":{},"title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<p>The character was placed in a situation where they had to choose between a trusted superior and their own ideals, and they chose to follow their ideals.</p><p></p><ul><li><p>ATTRIBUTE: +1 Reason</p></li><li><p>DEPARTMENT: + 1 Conn</p></li><li><p>FOCUS SUGGESTIONS: Uniform Code of Justice, History, Starfleet Protocol</p></li></ul>"},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"ownership":{"default":-1,"BsQYuBoOZwvCjdMe":3},"flags":{}}],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.sta.character-lifepath.PMrUNdc92HMFl9Xq"}},"_stats":{"coreVersion":"10.312","systemId":"sta","systemVersion":"1.2.5","createdTime":1722009509629,"modifiedTime":1724080569323,"lastModifiedBy":"6xWKidE3J8zSAagd"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6xWKidE3J8zSAagd":3},"_id":"XPRturw2MTzASVWq"}
{"name":"Conflict with a Hostile Culture","pages":[{"sort":100000,"name":"Conflict with a Hostile Culture","type":"text","_id":"7rajSMFoqPGjyCBc","system":{},"title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<p>The character was involved in a battle with a hostile force.</p><p></p><ul><li><p>ATTRIBUTE: +1 Fitness</p></li><li><p>DEPARTMENT: +1 Security</p></li><li><p>FOCUS SUGGESTIONS: Hand Phasers, Hand-to-Hand Combat, Tactical Systems</p></li></ul>"},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"ownership":{"default":-1,"BsQYuBoOZwvCjdMe":3},"flags":{}}],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.sta.character-lifepath.ViD2xbFWrLvr1joN"}},"_stats":{"coreVersion":"10.312","systemId":"sta","systemVersion":"1.2.5","createdTime":1722009520464,"modifiedTime":1724080570668,"lastModifiedBy":"6xWKidE3J8zSAagd"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6xWKidE3J8zSAagd":3},"_id":"sZ1iNSClpwLfZEWa"}
{"name":"Dealt with a Plague","pages":[{"sort":100000,"name":"Dealt with a Plague","type":"text","_id":"WjgzOvdvXIh4Gu62","system":{},"title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<p>The character’s ship was assigned to provide aid to a world dealing with an epidemic.</p><p></p><ul><li><p>ATTRIBUTE: +1 Insight</p></li><li><p>DEPARTMENT: + 1 Medicine</p></li><li><p>FOCUS SUGGESTIONS: Infectious Diseases, Emergency Medicine, Triage</p></li></ul>"},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"ownership":{"default":-1,"BsQYuBoOZwvCjdMe":3},"flags":{}}],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.sta.character-lifepath.pE6Vi9njUaximk2F"}},"_stats":{"coreVersion":"10.312","systemId":"sta","systemVersion":"1.2.5","createdTime":1722009537339,"modifiedTime":1724080572375,"lastModifiedBy":"6xWKidE3J8zSAagd"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6xWKidE3J8zSAagd":3},"_id":"u6ZkBT48GC2mZsap"}
{"name":"Death of a Friend","pages":[{"sort":100000,"name":"Death of a Friend","type":"text","_id":"fQvKPO6Cle8DzQJn","system":{},"title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<p>One of the character’s friends was killed in action.</p><p></p><ul><li><p>ATTRIBUTE: +1 Insight</p></li><li><p>DEPARTMENT: + 1 Medicine</p></li><li><p>FOCUS SUGGESTIONS: Counseling, but it may also represent a skill or pursuit the character takes up in their fallen friend’s memory</p></li></ul>"},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"ownership":{"default":-1,"BsQYuBoOZwvCjdMe":3},"flags":{}}],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.sta.character-lifepath.gaLz7L92cuhFMnKK"}},"_stats":{"coreVersion":"10.312","systemId":"sta","systemVersion":"1.2.5","createdTime":1722009548279,"modifiedTime":1724080573898,"lastModifiedBy":"6xWKidE3J8zSAagd"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6xWKidE3J8zSAagd":3},"_id":"yxuVpeCnA7v31mlz"}
{"name":"Discovered an Artifact","pages":[{"sort":100000,"name":"Discovered an Artifact","type":"text","_id":"3IegntbXToFxAFMu","system":{},"title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<p>The character discovered a device or fragment of technology from a now-extinct civilization.</p><p></p><ul><li><p>ATTRIBUTE: +1 Reason</p></li><li><p>DEPARTMENT: + 1 Engineering</p></li><li><p>FOCUS SUGGESTIONS: Ancient Technology, Computers, Reverse Engineering</p></li></ul>"},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"ownership":{"default":-1,"BsQYuBoOZwvCjdMe":3},"flags":{}}],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.sta.character-lifepath.CEDj1aHu8XXevAlm"}},"_stats":{"coreVersion":"10.312","systemId":"sta","systemVersion":"1.2.5","createdTime":1722009565128,"modifiedTime":1724080575361,"lastModifiedBy":"6xWKidE3J8zSAagd"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6xWKidE3J8zSAagd":3},"_id":"1gpSCU1g0ERThJH6"}
{"name":"Encountered a Truly Alien Being","pages":[{"sort":100000,"name":"Encountered a Truly Alien Being","type":"text","_id":"vZw8L9ZGBQLfuN4s","system":{},"title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<p>The character encountered a life-form which is truly alien, something barely within the comprehension of humanoid life. It might have been some godlike entity, or a creature that swims through space, but whatever it was, it was not life as we know it.</p><p></p><ul><li><p>ATTRIBUTE: +1 Reason</p></li><li><p>DEPARTMENT: + 1 Science</p></li><li><p>FOCUS SUGGESTIONS: Empathy, Philosophy, Xenobiology</p></li></ul>"},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"ownership":{"default":-1,"BsQYuBoOZwvCjdMe":3},"flags":{}}],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.sta.character-lifepath.toNtb7y5s1c3ZIYR"}},"_stats":{"coreVersion":"10.312","systemId":"sta","systemVersion":"1.2.5","createdTime":1722009577535,"modifiedTime":1724080576665,"lastModifiedBy":"6xWKidE3J8zSAagd"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6xWKidE3J8zSAagd":3},"_id":"FMQfNBR2ImkA7rJY"}
{"name":"First Contact","pages":[{"sort":100000,"name":"First Contact","type":"text","_id":"h4x1mgVlEoyoACTj","system":{},"title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<p>The character was involved in one of the most important of Starfleet’s missions: first contact with another culture.</p><p></p><ul><li><p>ATTRIBUTE: +1 Presence</p></li><li><p>DEPARTMENT: + 1 Any</p></li><li><p>FOCUS SUGGESTIONS: Cultural Studies, Diplomacy, Infiltration</p></li></ul>"},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"ownership":{"default":-1,"BsQYuBoOZwvCjdMe":3},"flags":{}}],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.sta.character-lifepath.WCXH2xA9mxXnnVIK"}},"_stats":{"coreVersion":"10.312","systemId":"sta","systemVersion":"1.2.5","createdTime":1722009592240,"modifiedTime":1724080579049,"lastModifiedBy":"6xWKidE3J8zSAagd"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6xWKidE3J8zSAagd":3},"_id":"O5N6QioFHM9ytLTt"}
{"name":"Lauded by Another Culture","pages":[{"sort":100000,"name":"Lauded by Another Culture","type":"text","_id":"vWJxml0SEmMm1UXO","system":{},"title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<p>The character was involved in a mission that earned the official praise of a non-Federation culture; they are now considered to be a friend to those people.</p><p></p><ul><li><p>ATTRIBUTE: +1 Presence</p></li><li><p>DEPARTMENT: + 1 Science</p></li><li><p>FOCUS SUGGESTIONS: A focus of X Culture, replacing the X with the name of that culture or any that represent skills or techniques specific to that culture.</p></li><li><p>TRAIT: A good example might be Friend to the X, replacing the X with the name of the culture. This reflects the character’s renown among that culture, and the benefits and problems such status brings.</p></li></ul>"},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"ownership":{"default":-1,"BsQYuBoOZwvCjdMe":3},"flags":{}}],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.sta.character-lifepath.cEZ6YNsrywz8gfib"}},"_stats":{"coreVersion":"10.312","systemId":"sta","systemVersion":"1.2.5","createdTime":1722009603399,"modifiedTime":1724080580256,"lastModifiedBy":"6xWKidE3J8zSAagd"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6xWKidE3J8zSAagd":3},"_id":"SypEWmRHiVGF42ci"}
{"name":"Learned Unique Language","pages":[{"sort":100000,"name":"Learned Unique Language","type":"text","_id":"Lns7QSyI8oZpJXSD","system":{},"title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<p>The character encounters a species with an unusual form of communication and learns to communicate with them.</p><p></p><ul><li><p>ATTRIBUTE: +1 Insight</p></li><li><p>DEPARTMENT: + 1 Science</p></li><li><p>FOCUS SUGGESTIONS: Linguistics, Cultural Studies, Negotiations</p></li></ul>"},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"ownership":{"default":-1,"BsQYuBoOZwvCjdMe":3},"flags":{}}],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.sta.character-lifepath.ooh6WNDEqu9ZGMUS"}},"_stats":{"coreVersion":"10.312","systemId":"sta","systemVersion":"1.2.5","createdTime":1722009613803,"modifiedTime":1724080582322,"lastModifiedBy":"6xWKidE3J8zSAagd"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6xWKidE3J8zSAagd":3},"_id":"F1CrzasKNoldvKPc"}
{"name":"Mentored","pages":[{"sort":100000,"name":"Mentored","type":"text","_id":"w0NK0NAdmFreGi9C","system":{},"title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<p>A highly-respected officer took notice of the character’s career. For a time, the character served as the officer’s pilot and aide, gaining the benefit of the officer’s experiences and lessons.</p><p></p><ul><li><p>ATTRIBUTE: +1 Any</p></li><li><p>DEPARTMENT: + 1 Conn</p></li><li><p>FOCUS SUGGESTIONS: Composure or Etiquette, any focus reflecting the officer’s specialties</p></li></ul>"},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"ownership":{"default":-1,"BsQYuBoOZwvCjdMe":3},"flags":{}}],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.sta.character-lifepath.PdIa1t6S3tPnyj5p"}},"_stats":{"coreVersion":"10.312","systemId":"sta","systemVersion":"1.2.5","createdTime":1722009623454,"modifiedTime":1724080584135,"lastModifiedBy":"6xWKidE3J8zSAagd"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6xWKidE3J8zSAagd":3},"_id":"kUH2CkE4xRlw6MuJ"}
{"name":"Negotiated a Treaty","pages":[{"sort":100000,"name":"Negotiated a Treaty","type":"text","_id":"i9vJZz4pxWyknW2z","system":{},"title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<p>The character was part of a delegation that helped negotiate a treaty, agreement, or alliance with a culture outside the Federation.</p><p></p><ul><li><p>ATTRIBUTE: +1 Control</p></li><li><p>DEPARTMENT: + 1 Command</p></li><li><p>FOCUS SUGGESTIONS: Diplomacy, Negotiation, Galactic Politics</p></li></ul>"},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"ownership":{"default":-1,"BsQYuBoOZwvCjdMe":3},"flags":{}}],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.sta.character-lifepath.vzEjDk42S6dKYS3s"}},"_stats":{"coreVersion":"10.312","systemId":"sta","systemVersion":"1.2.5","createdTime":1722009634246,"modifiedTime":1724080585695,"lastModifiedBy":"6xWKidE3J8zSAagd"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6xWKidE3J8zSAagd":3},"_id":"FD0qbcYfVPZxXi6g"}
{"name":"New Battle Strategy","pages":[{"sort":100000,"name":"New Battle Strategy","type":"text","_id":"p7bOuPeBfQyimnBf","system":{},"title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<p>In combat with a hostile force, the character devised a new strategy or tactic.</p><p></p><ul><li><p>ATTRIBUTE: +1 Daring</p></li><li><p>DEPARTMENT: + 1 Security</p></li><li><p>FOCUS SUGGESTIONS: Combat Tactics or Hazard Awareness</p></li></ul>"},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"ownership":{"default":-1,"BsQYuBoOZwvCjdMe":3},"flags":{}}],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.sta.character-lifepath.eWtNjbonctgcn1Kw"}},"_stats":{"coreVersion":"10.312","systemId":"sta","systemVersion":"1.2.5","createdTime":1722009645550,"modifiedTime":1724080587052,"lastModifiedBy":"6xWKidE3J8zSAagd"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6xWKidE3J8zSAagd":3},"_id":"V6F1MtUw5WzM0L1m"}
{"name":"Required to Take Command","pages":[{"sort":100000,"name":"Required to Take Command","type":"text","_id":"PyFeRlqsaRcQxNb5","system":{},"title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<p>During a mission, a crisis left the mission’s leader unable to lead. This required the character to take command, something they may not have been prepared for.</p><p></p><ul><li><p>ATTRIBUTE: +1 Daring</p></li><li><p>DEPARTMENT: + 1 Command</p></li><li><p>FOCUS SUGGESTIONS: Inspiration or Composure</p></li></ul>"},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"ownership":{"default":-1,"BsQYuBoOZwvCjdMe":3},"flags":{}}],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.sta.character-lifepath.nP3P3Sr1NqSPIuKa"}},"_stats":{"coreVersion":"10.312","systemId":"sta","systemVersion":"1.2.5","createdTime":1722009659789,"modifiedTime":1724080588646,"lastModifiedBy":"6xWKidE3J8zSAagd"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6xWKidE3J8zSAagd":3},"_id":"I9OtUt36KpcQwfDF"}
{"name":"Serious Injury","pages":[{"sort":100000,"name":"Serious Injury","type":"text","_id":"XuFXylFdJ26m4fX6","system":{},"title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<p>The character was seriously hurt and needed to spend a considerable amount of time recovering.</p><p></p><ul><li><p>ATTRIBUTE: +1 Fitness</p></li><li><p>DEPARTMENT: + 1 Medicine</p></li><li><p>FOCUS SUGGESTIONS: The focus should reflect the circumstances of the character’s injury, something that helped them through recovery, or something they took up after recovering.</p></li><li><p>TRAIT: The character may gain a trait, which should reflect some lasting effect of the character’s injury or the way they recovered. Examples: Prosthetic Implant or some form of disability.</p></li></ul>"},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"ownership":{"default":-1,"BsQYuBoOZwvCjdMe":3},"flags":{}}],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.sta.character-lifepath.OU2S6JwbTKaxSwtH"}},"_stats":{"coreVersion":"10.312","systemId":"sta","systemVersion":"1.2.5","createdTime":1722009675340,"modifiedTime":1724080590128,"lastModifiedBy":"6xWKidE3J8zSAagd"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6xWKidE3J8zSAagd":3},"_id":"0tAhmDmFZD3yt28H"}
{"name":"Service Roles","pages":[{"sort":100000,"name":"Service Roles","type":"text","_id":"6PAVJ8Mz9jEoRVNS","system":{},"title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<p>The following roles are found within Starfleet in all eras of play, unless otherwise noted. Non-Starfleet characters in similar organizations (e.g., the Klingon Defense Force or Romulan Imperial Navy) may select from this list of roles as well, gaining the same benefit.</p>"},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"ownership":{"default":-1,"BsQYuBoOZwvCjdMe":3},"flags":{}},{"sort":200000,"name":"Commanding Officer","type":"text","_id":"QD9sZ9FT946xWCWL","system":{},"title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<p>Even if the commanding officer does not hold the rank of captain, they are usually referred to as captain by their subordinates aboard a starship. Aboard stations, commanding officers are referred to by their rank. </p><p>Commanding officers are responsible for the ship or facility under their command as well as executing the orders and directives from their leadership.</p><p></p><p>ROLE BENEFIT: You may spend Determination to grant any other character you can communicate with 1 Determination; this does not have to be linked to using or challenging a value.</p>"},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"ownership":{"default":-1,"BsQYuBoOZwvCjdMe":3},"flags":{}},{"sort":300000,"name":"Executive Officer","type":"text","_id":"WPpCDe1Oyj77qrcb","system":{},"title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<p>Second-in-command. The executive officer is the captain’s chief advisor and takes command in situations where the captain is unable to. If a ship does not have a dedicated executive officer, an officer in another role should be noted as second-in-command, but they will not gain the benefits of this role.</p><p></p><p>ROLE BENEFIT: When an allied character in communication with you spends Determination, you may spend 3 Momentum (Immediate) to enable that character to regain the spent point of Determination.</p>"},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"ownership":{"default":-1,"BsQYuBoOZwvCjdMe":3},"flags":{}},{"sort":400000,"name":"Operations Manager","type":"text","_id":"XNVQnCC1W6MNWiUC","system":{},"title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<p>The operations manager manages and oversees all technical operations aboard or involving the ship, normally from the operations station on the bridge, or in conjunction with the chief engineer (on smaller ships, one officer may fill both roles). This often entails taking on the duties of a science officer if there is no dedicated science officer among the senior staff.</p><p></p><p>ROLE BENEFIT: Whenever you create a trait representing a piece of equipment, or an alteration made to existing equipment, any character who benefits from that trait while you are present in the scene may re-roll a d20.</p>"},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"ownership":{"default":-1,"BsQYuBoOZwvCjdMe":3},"flags":{}},{"sort":500000,"name":"Chief Engineer","type":"text","_id":"Vx7oMNo1lHgRZ8CO","system":{},"title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<p>The chief engineer is responsible for ensuring the ship remains operational and functional, and commands the engineering department aboard the ship.</p><p></p><p>ROLE BENEFIT: You reduce the opportunity cost of engineering teams by 1, to a minimum of 0. Further, when you attempt a task to perform repairs to a starship or attempt to push the ship’s capabilities beyond its normal limits, you may spend 1 Momentum (Immediate) to re-roll a d20.</p>"},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"ownership":{"default":-1,"BsQYuBoOZwvCjdMe":3},"flags":{}},{"sort":600000,"name":"Chief of Security","type":"text","_id":"mlQSMdDSTiX5GJEb","system":{},"title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<p>The chief of security oversees the ship’s security department and is responsible for ensuring the safety of the ship and crew during missions, for the investigation of disciplinary and criminal matters, and for overseeing the protection of important persons aboard the ship.</p><p></p><p>ROLE BENEFIT: You reduce the opportunity cost of weapons and security teams by 1, to a minimum of 0. Further, when you succeed at an Attack against an enemy during personal combat, you may spend 1 Momentum to increase the Difficulty of that enemy’s next Attack by 1.</p>"},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"ownership":{"default":-1,"BsQYuBoOZwvCjdMe":3},"flags":{}},{"sort":700000,"name":"Chief Tactical Officer","type":"text","_id":"qlCALQJ3hobeTO8z","system":{},"title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<p>A presence on 22nd and 23rd century Starfleet ships, and common in other organizations, this role is also known as an armory officer or weapons officer. The officer is responsible for the upkeep and use of the ship’s armaments and is typically an expert in ship-to-ship combat.</p><p></p><p>ROLE BENEFIT: When you succeed at an Attack with the ship’s weapons, you may increase the damage rating of that weapon system by spending 1 Momentum rather than 2.</p>"},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"ownership":{"default":-1,"BsQYuBoOZwvCjdMe":3},"flags":{}},{"sort":800000,"name":"Flight Controller","type":"text","_id":"jlND0Qp7bilq1VNQ","system":{},"title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<p>Also known as a helmsman on 22nd and 23rd century Starfleet vessels. Not a typical senior staff role, though some captains, particularly those operating in uncharted space, choose the most senior helmsman or flight control officer to serve on the senior staff.</p><p></p><p>ROLE BENEFIT: When you attempt an engineering task related to flight or propulsion, you may use your Conn rating instead of Engineering. When you succeed at a Conn task to pilot a starship, you generate 1 bonus Momentum to be used on that task (bonus Momentum may not be saved).</p>"},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"ownership":{"default":-1,"BsQYuBoOZwvCjdMe":3},"flags":{}},{"sort":900000,"name":"Navigator","type":"text","_id":"kvUAX77tA48O3pZn","system":{},"title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<p>On vessels exploring the uncharted frontiers of space, a skilled navigator, astrometrics officer, or stellar cartographer plots courses, studies and updates astrometrics charts and data, and supports the helmsman or flight controller. Navigators are rarely called to serve on the senior staff.</p><p></p><p>ROLE BENEFIT: When you attempt a science task related to astrophysics or stellar navigation, you may use your Conn rating instead of Science. When you attempt or Assist a task to maneuver a starship through difficult or dangerous terrain, you may spend 1 Momentum to ignore a complication suffered (Repeatable).</p>"},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"ownership":{"default":-1,"BsQYuBoOZwvCjdMe":3},"flags":{}},{"sort":1000000,"name":"Science Officer","type":"text","_id":"iVgClMVO4YsCi0dT","system":{},"title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<p>The science officer (sometimes referred to as the chief science officer) is responsible for advising the commanding officer on all scientific matters, providing hypotheses concerning the unknown. The science officer is also responsible for all science personnel on the ship or station.</p><p></p><p>ROLE BENEFIT: When you succeed at a task assisted by the ship’s Sensors or Computers, or a task using a tricorder or other sensing device, you may ask one additional question as if you had spent Momentum on Obtain Information.</p>"},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"ownership":{"default":-1,"BsQYuBoOZwvCjdMe":3},"flags":{}},{"sort":1100000,"name":"Chief Medical Officer","type":"text","_id":"Lrg07DdtE3z8b7iv","system":{},"title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<p>The chief medical officer is responsible for the health and well-being of the crew and other people aboard the ship and leads the ship’s medical department. A chief medical officer can order, and countermand the orders of, senior officers where matters of that officer’s health are concerned. In extreme situations, the chief medical officer can declare an officer unfit and remove them from active duty (including the commanding officer). A ship may have either a chief medical officer or a ship’s doctor.</p><p></p><p>ROLE BENEFIT: You reduce the opportunity cost of medical equipment and medical teams by 1, to a minimum of 0. Further, when you attempt a task using your Medicine rating, and you have assistance, you generate 1 bonus Momentum (bonus Momentum may not be saved).</p>"},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"ownership":{"default":-1,"BsQYuBoOZwvCjdMe":3},"flags":{}},{"sort":1200000,"name":"Ship's Doctor","type":"text","_id":"5f2D8GoB6CciSVkM","system":{},"title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<p>You care for the crew of your ship, or the station you serve on (in which case, rename the role to Station’s Doctor), but unlike a chief medical officer, you do not have an extensive medical department to manage or to aid you. This is common in smaller crews which do not require a large sickbay or infirmary and tends to mean these smaller postings favor generalists who can adapt to a variety of circumstances.</p><p>A ship may have either a chief medical officer or a ship’s doctor.</p><p></p><p>ROLE BENEFIT: You have two additional focuses, which must relate to medicine fields of study. However, your ship cannot use Crew Support to introduce supporting characters who are medical personnel.</p>"},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"ownership":{"default":-1,"BsQYuBoOZwvCjdMe":3},"flags":{}},{"sort":1300000,"name":"Ship's (or Station's) Counselor","type":"text","_id":"YdeoFQWgEEDbp6BU","system":{},"title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<p>On larger ships and starbases, it’s common (especially in the 24th century and beyond) to have personnel dedicated to the mental well-being of the crew. Some captains regard them as valuable advisors, as their training covers both culture and psychology, making them exceptionally good at reading the moods and intentions of others.</p><p></p><p>ROLE BENEFIT: When you Assist a character suffering from a trait representing a negative emotional state, you may re-roll your assist die. Additionally, once per mission, you may spend a scene counseling a character who has challenged one of their values during the current mission. At the end of the scene, the character may rewrite their crossed-out value immediately, rather than waiting until the end of the mission. If they do this, they immediately gain 1 Determination as well.</p>"},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"ownership":{"default":-1,"BsQYuBoOZwvCjdMe":3},"flags":{}},{"sort":1400000,"name":"Communications Officer","type":"text","_id":"SdWLzdXRKFaCkrAT","system":{},"title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<p>More common in the earlier days of Starfleet, dedicated communications officers are typically skilled in linguistics and cryptography, and aided with advanced translation and decryption technologies, and are valuable during encounters with new cultures, hostile or otherwise.</p><p></p><p>ROLE BENEFIT: When you attempt a task assisted by the ship’s Computers or Communications systems, do not roll the ship’s assist die: instead, count the ship’s die as if it had rolled a 1.</p>"},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"ownership":{"default":-1,"BsQYuBoOZwvCjdMe":3},"flags":{}}],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.sta.character-lifepath.mOfVft5wVXr4Uv2K"}},"_stats":{"coreVersion":"10.312","systemId":"sta","systemVersion":"1.2.5","createdTime":1722352121621,"modifiedTime":1724080591638,"lastModifiedBy":"6xWKidE3J8zSAagd"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6xWKidE3J8zSAagd":3},"_id":"NuzjRdIQA5ap56qe"}
{"name":"Ship Destroyed","pages":[{"sort":100000,"name":"Ship Destroyed","type":"text","_id":"wFwaDkPcKzZJ6Ys2","system":{},"title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<p>The ship the character was serving on was destroyed during a mission, and the character was one of the few who survived.</p><p></p><ul><li><p>ATTRIBUTE: +1 Daring</p></li><li><p>DEPARTMENT: + 1 Security</p></li><li><p>FOCUS SUGGESTIONS: Extra Vehicular Operations, Small Craft, Survival</p></li></ul>"},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"ownership":{"default":-1,"BsQYuBoOZwvCjdMe":3},"flags":{}}],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.sta.character-lifepath.DRsQPhNFVcOY9612"}},"_stats":{"coreVersion":"10.312","systemId":"sta","systemVersion":"1.2.5","createdTime":1722009687879,"modifiedTime":1724080593001,"lastModifiedBy":"6xWKidE3J8zSAagd"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6xWKidE3J8zSAagd":3},"_id":"0uO1YbENmsaSr7Fr"}
{"name":"Solved an Engineering Crisis","pages":[{"sort":100000,"name":"Solved an Engineering Crisis","type":"text","_id":"tj4cUNt843qeKOp0","system":{},"title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<p>The character was instrumental in ending a crisis caused by malfunctioning technology and saved many lives in the process.</p><p></p><ul><li><p>ATTRIBUTE: +1 Control</p></li><li><p>DEPARTMENT: + 1 Engineering</p></li><li><p>FOCUS SUGGESTIONS: Electro-Plasma Power Systems, Fusion Reactors, Warp Engines</p></li></ul>"},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"ownership":{"default":-1,"BsQYuBoOZwvCjdMe":3},"flags":{}}],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.sta.character-lifepath.ZCehMZxo0jbcB9Np"}},"_stats":{"coreVersion":"10.312","systemId":"sta","systemVersion":"1.2.5","createdTime":1722009701270,"modifiedTime":1724080594536,"lastModifiedBy":"6xWKidE3J8zSAagd"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6xWKidE3J8zSAagd":3},"_id":"LvdJdc9yY5ic2VAr"}
{"name":"Special Commendation","pages":[{"sort":100000,"name":"Special Commendation","type":"text","_id":"2C9YyagOlzrOH0nx","system":{},"title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<p>During a crisis, the character saved the lives of several colleagues, helping them to safety. This earned the character a special commendation.</p><p></p><ul><li><p>ATTRIBUTE: +1 Fitness</p></li><li><p>DEPARTMENT: + 1 Any</p></li><li><p>FOCUS SUGGESTIONS: Athletics, Survival, Emergency Medicine</p></li></ul>"},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"ownership":{"default":-1,"BsQYuBoOZwvCjdMe":3},"flags":{}}],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.sta.character-lifepath.hMoC4qRr1a2y5hWx"}},"_stats":{"coreVersion":"10.312","systemId":"sta","systemVersion":"1.2.5","createdTime":1722009714003,"modifiedTime":1724080596156,"lastModifiedBy":"6xWKidE3J8zSAagd"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6xWKidE3J8zSAagd":3},"_id":"hpeK71LbccTr6AMH"}
{"name":"Transporter Accident","pages":[{"sort":100000,"name":"Transporter Accident","type":"text","_id":"btgrhKLaF5924Hwx","system":{},"title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<p>The character suffered some manner of strange accident while using a transporter.</p><p></p><ul><li><p>ATTRIBUTE: +1 Control</p></li><li><p>DEPARTMENT: + 1 Conn</p></li><li><p>FOCUS SUGGESTIONS: Transporters &amp; Replicators, Small Craft, Quantum Mechanics</p></li></ul>"},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"ownership":{"default":-1,"BsQYuBoOZwvCjdMe":3},"flags":{}}],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.sta.character-lifepath.vEdj24qdJPxibE9E"}},"_stats":{"coreVersion":"10.312","systemId":"sta","systemVersion":"1.2.5","createdTime":1722009727655,"modifiedTime":1724080597690,"lastModifiedBy":"6xWKidE3J8zSAagd"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6xWKidE3J8zSAagd":3},"_id":"0xFUusVBaFSG95V4"}
